Title: Pushing Back
Description: Eliminate the Infernal Corrupted in Vehemence and Iratus, detonate the Anti-Corruption Bombs, and recover any supplies left behind. Then report back to Warden Reese in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It feels like the Corrupted keep getting stronger - I'm not sure how much longer we can defend this spot.\n\nEvery day, they push us farther from the mountain, and any chance of striking at the source.
InProgressResponse: Weaken the Corrupted's position in Vehemence and Iratus so we can get supplies through to Mountainrise. \n\nReclaim any supplies you find in those forts as well.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: That was quite impressive, but somehow I'm not surprised. Now we can finally re-establish supply lines with Mountainrise.\n\nAnd Charity's been hoping to recover some of this Orichalcum and Starmetal.

Title: Our Own Worst Enemy
Description: Search for Soulwarden Heartgems across the five forts in Shattered Mountain, and search for any Corrupted writings. Then report back to Ranger Madaki in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Bah, same as they do in the Cleave and everywhere else - they turn our own against us.\n\nThat's right, every time a Soulwarden falls, a Corrupted rises in their place. We're fighting our comrades out there.
InProgressResponse: Get me as many Heartgems as you can find and any Corrupted Writings. \n\nHonestly, it's the only chance we've got to stop this madness.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well I'll be damned, you got more Heartgems than I expected. Sad is what that is.\n\nBut let's see these writings... hm, this is interesting - it's written by a Warden as he was falling to the Corruption.

Title: The Illurmin Rift
Description: Explore the deadly Illurmin Rift and deliver your discoveries to Warden Linch in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, but I wouldn't take the road.\n\nThere's some vile Corrupted down in the Illurmin Rift, like something straight from hell, and I worry they're prepping to attack both here and in Mountainrise.
InProgressResponse: The things coming out of the Rift are scary enough to make you mess your smallclothes if you're not prepared.\n\nHave courage, and for azoth's sake, watch your back.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I'll be a weathered knob on an Angry Spriggan's arse! Someone finally made it through!\n\nFirst one to come in from Mountainhome in quite some time, and through the Illurmin Rift, to boot!

Title: Guardians' Secrets
Description: Defeat Guardian Tzi-Wang, recover Baetylus Luckstones, and defeat Rockruins Guardians in Spilaio Cavern. Then report back to Warden Reese in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Well, I'm no nerdy researcher like William Heron, but you have to admit - those Ancients knew some things.\n\nThe Corrupted actually give some of the old ruins a wide berth.
InProgressResponse: Spilaio Cavern is certainly a hike, I know... but it's worth a shot.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Hey, you made it back! That bony wretch didn't give you too much trouble, I hope? \n\nAnd what are these? Baetylus Luckstones? I wonder if that's what repels the Corruption. William Heron, never around when you need him.

Title: Alligator Steaks
Description: Hunt Shattered Alligators for Gator Steaks and seek out bundles of Mirespice Blend held by the Desolate Scroungers. Then report back to Warden Douglas in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I've been trying to think of a way to cheer people up, but it's just not a cheery place.\n\nMaybe those weird steaks some of the Rangers eat? With the right spice, who knows?
InProgressResponse: Shattered Gator Meat and Mirespice Blend, and then we'll be cooking… or is it better to eat it raw?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: I don't know if I'm excited or a little nervous to see you return.\n\nBut we've all been subsisting on dry rations around here, so I'll even eat alligator. Mmm. I'll prepare it, at least.

Title: Malevolent Offerings
Description: End the rituals in Lapsus and Pullus by eliminating the Corrupted Vicars, their guards, and their Corruption Barbs, then reclaim their Corrupted ritual implements. Then report back to Warden Linch in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Aye, and now we fight for our very souls, and those of every living creature on the face of the Earth.\n\nThe Corrupted here are practicing dark magics that we can't comprehend... but we damn well better put a stop to.
InProgressResponse: Whatever it takes, break up those rituals, destroy the Vicars, and take the implements of their evil. \n\nThat way they can't recreate their rituals even if they come back.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Finally, an end to those infernal rituals! I can feel the difference already. We all can\n\nWhatever they were doing, it was driving us mad. You've saved this fort from certain doom, I tell you.

Title: Mountainrise Offensive
Description: Defeat Dau-Shin and recover Armor Scraps from the Rockrift Carvers in Spilaio Cavern. Then report back to Warden Fayed in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm glad you agree. Before we make a drive, however, we have to make ourselves less vulnerable.\n\nThe weapons the Corrupted wield seem to slice through our armor like it's not even there.
InProgressResponse: If we can get some of the armor from the Cavern, it will help us battle the Corrupted.\n\nDau-Shin must be defeated first.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha, a successful mission, I presume? Yes, Dau-Shin defeated and these armor scraps will do nicely.\n\nI will see them broken down and used to reinforce the Warden's armors. Then, my friend... then we will strike.

Title: Knowledge is Power
Description: Extract the essence of the Bitterblade Corrupted at Odium fort, and get a fresh sample from a Blight Nodule near Putridspores in the Blighted Wilds. Then report back to Ranger Herath in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: We know some of the Corrupted in Edengrove have proven susceptible to the Blight.\n\nThe Corrupted near the Mountain are of a different class altogether, but perhaps they suffer from the same weakness.
InProgressResponse: If you can get me Corrupted Essence and fresh Blight samples, I can do the rest.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha, the procurer of the ingredients for my experiment!\n\nLet us see how these elements interact… yes, the Corruption certainly can't take hold, and in fact, it is weakened. This will work.

Title: Blight Resistance
Description: Collect a Blight Sample from the Hidden Strain and defeat Fay, the Last Protector. Bring a piece of his remains to Ranger Herath in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ah, now that you mention it, I did notice some Angry Earth in the region that seem impervious.\n\nThey are led by a particularly fierce Dryad simply known as Fay - I suspect he would be trouble, even for you.
InProgressResponse: Fay and his band of Dryads are a force unto themselves.\n\nProceed with caution - my hopes go with you.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Wait, you faced down Fay and survived to return? I must confess, I had my doubts.\n\nI am very happy to see they were unfounded. Now, let's see what we can learn from what you've recovered.

Title: Path to Myrkgard
Description: Travel to Myrkgard and destroy the Corrupted Monoliths and Portals, collecting the Orbs hidden at each. Combine the Orbs with Captain Thorpe's Corrupted Aura to form the Myrkgard Arena Key, unlocking the Arena behind the Myrkgard Cathedral.\n\n[This Quest can be shared and repeated.]
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed. We believe the Tempest is down beneath the ruins of Myrkgard, but getting in there won't be easy. \n\nWe believe the only way to enter the portals from which we see the Corrupted emerging.
InProgressResponse: Make sure to rally some other Wardens to your side, and then collect the Orbs from the Monoliths.\n\nThat will open the portal to take you… who knows where. If anyone can do this, you can. Godspeed, Warden.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0717_0101_myrkgardarena_complete_available_response

Title: Madaki's Stratagem
Description: Search the forges of Caminus for any weapon molds or crucibles they might be using to forge weapons of great power. Then report back to Ranger Madaki in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Possibly, but there seem to be some unique molds involved in the process.\n\nIf the Corrupted are attempting to forge such things, it would be in the forges of Caminus. Someone will need to go there.
InProgressResponse: If it is possible to use these Ancient forging techniques, we'll need whatever molds or crucibles they're using at the forges of Caminus.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You've returned. I'm impressed and cautiously optimistic. You found the crucibles?\n\nAmazing. With these, we can forge a great variety of weapon types. I will share them amongst all the Rangers and Wardens.

Title: Baetylus Headpiece (Expedition)
Description: Defeat the Cilla in the Lazarus Instrumentality Expedition and Collect the Naga Headdress. Then report back to Warden Reese in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Definitely a dodgy place, in Reekwater. If you can find others as mad as you, it might be worth it.\n\nLegends say there's some Naga in there, headpiece made of Baetylus… could be quite useful.
InProgressResponse: Are you really going to venture into the Lazarus Instrumentality…?\n\nJust be careful. I think we still need you in the fight against Corruption.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Welcome back to the front, {playerName}. Wait, the Lazarus Instrumentality? You can't mean…\n\nWell I'll be a sea turtle's nephew… you got the Naga Headdress too? I guess we'll have to get this looked at. Amazing work!

Title: Ultimate Blight Defense (Expedition)
Description: Defeat the Alluvium Marl and Collect Alluvium Spores for Ranger Herath in Shattered Mountain.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, a sacred place for the Angry Earth, perhaps the most sacred.\n\nThere is said to be a… "thing" there, so organically potent, its spores can protect against anything.
InProgressResponse: The Alluvium Marl in the Garden of Genesis… \n\nI have no idea what to expect… other than it being likely one of the most dangerous creatures in all Aeternum.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well, this is truly beyond the pale - you're the first I've seen venture into the Garden and return.\n\nYou got the Alluvium spores as well? These… now these will give us the upper hand. Well done!

Title: Forging Twilight's Fall
Description: Recover the components needed to forge Twilight's Fall and deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I can only decipher what's needed for the blade... Twilight's Fall, as I've taken to calling it.\n\nCollecting these elements will take you all over Aeternum. Are you certain you wish to undertake this?
InProgressResponse: You have undertaken a long journey, my friend.\n\nBut I believe Twilight's Fall will be a weapon fit for a warrior-poet. Godspeed.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, I see you've taken over Ranger Demir's work, acquiring the elements for Twilight's Fall.\n\nYes, this is the blade of champions. Wield it with pride. It suits you well. But you will want a shield to accompany it, yes?

Title: Forging Boundless Ward
Description: Recover the components needed to forge Boundles Ward and deliver them to Ranger Madaki in Mountainhome.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: @0720_0101_BW_00_proposal
InProgressResponse: A longsword without a sister shield is like a missing limb. \n\nStart your journey with confidence. I look forward to your return and testing my smithing skills.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You're back, good. With these materials I can forge the strongest shield in all of Aeternum. \n\nThere…. Boundless Ward. This will defend against Corruption, and anything else, for that matter.

Title: Scorched Mines
Description: Venture to Ambusti Superior in Shattered Mountains. The Corrupted have vital raw materials needed to forge Boundless Ward.

Title: Tangled Tribulations
Description: Travel to The Tangle within Mrykgard and recover materials for Boundless Ward's grip.

Title: Upper Harrows
Description: The Myrkgard's weapon stores lie deeper within. Defeat the Corrupted and acquire broken shields to construct your own.

Title: Divine Opulence
Description: Conquer the Darkness and slay Archmagister Vocus for his protective charm.

Title: A Spear to Pierce the Heavens
Description: The odyssey of an unnamed Ancient Guardian, trace their steps and find clues for the Heavensplitter.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Indeed, it is the story of an Ancient Guardian who undertook an odyssey for this weapon. \n\nFollow the poem wherever it leads, and bring what you find to Madaki, and earn yourself a spear that will pierce the sky.
InProgressResponse: The Heavensplitter, could it be from the Heavens? Or the deepest pits of the Underworld?\n\nEither way, it will be a weapon of great power.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, the elements needed to forge the revered spear. A beautiful poem, wasn't it?\n\nVery well, this shall be a weapon above all others. Behold… the 'Heavensplitter'! Even the skys cannot hold you down, now.

Title: Recollection of a Journey
Description: I saw in the sky the beauty of the heavens, marveling at the sight of stars and the dance of lights. As I drew lines between the heavenly bodies, I split the heavens with my finger. I shared with my comrades the stories of these beings in the sky, as well as my own story. Such stories precede my birth, and will survive me for ages.

Title: Book One: Nostos
Description: As I began my journey, I found first myself searching in the cays at the foot of the island. It took me to the top of a magnificent tower, and I pondered how our yearning for the sky drives the construction of these towers. To Holm, I entrusted my post, and visited the caverns south.

Title: Book Two: Elegeia
Description: The stars above the caverns pointed me northeast. There, I found an isle that was closer to the Underworld than anything I ever seen. I descended into a realm where my soul was torn asunder by Hades himself. There, I fought his hellhound, and from that frothy maw stole a gem sky blue. I knew it was a sign.

Title: Book Three: Parodos
Description: As I trekked the Underworld, I found myself in its swamps. The chorus of voices crying out rang through the fog. I could sense the souls of those around me, and yet I could do naught but listen. Phantoms calling out in song, not unlike the Kokytos. I knew that I must transport this gem as a trial, and succeed where others have failed.

Title: Book Four: Akron
Description: I waded through the swamps and, like a siren's song, I again found myself at another tower. I saw beings of the earth, the dryads, patrolling Eridanus that was entrusted to them. At its humble base, I shared the gem with these primordial protectors. They anointed it with a tear of azoth whose purity was unmatched. What a brilliant sight.

Title: Book Five: Istia
Description: My journey was becoming clearer to me. To pierce the sky, the fates were bringing me to the many towers that dot the island. It brought me then to a tower in the valley of mourning. The tower stood like a solemn watcher. I met with the soldier at the top, and shared with him my story. To find a kindred soldier on this island is rare.

Title: Book Six: Pyrgos
Description: The final tower the fates brought me to was one ruled by the earth, and the dryads that protect it. In a land that birthed life here on this island, I climbed the tower searching for guidance. The guardians there tested my strength, and rewarded my spirit with a spearshaft made of an ancient, blessed wood.

Title: Book Seven: Hesukhia
Description: My journey was coming to a close, my ultimate test was found the badlands choked by red: the Mangled Heights. I stood at the summit. I fastened sharp tendrils to the spearshaft, and affixed the skygem to purify my spear. I took my spear and leapt to the heavens, splitting them in pieces. Day shattered, giving its fractured lights to the Night sky, and I rested among the stars.

Title: Aria of a Frozen Lament
Description: The song and dance of a legendary rapier whose steps must be followed precisely to complete.
PlayerPrompt: "I heard from Madaki that you're an expert with a rapier."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: To wield a rapier is to know the dance of combat, the sweeping highs and lows of dexterous swordplay. There is one such blade that we can put together with reagents from across the island.
InProgressResponse: Never look down upon the noble career of a dancer as frivolous, for you must become one to flourish and twirl this tempered orichalcum razor. \n\nYour enemies will quiver in fear to see your beautiful, ever-evolving, monstrous movements.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This weapon is powerful indeed, and it is yours to look after now. \n\nTake it; go forth and send the Corrupted to an icy hell colder than the broken mountain they occupy.

Title: Frostbitten Cabriole
Description: A Cabriole: A jump to The Tangle.

Title: Icy Arabesque
Description: An Arabesque: A position on one leg with the other behind in Malevolence.

Title: Seaside Echappé
Description: An Echappé: A jump from first, third, or fifth position to second or fourth position and returning to Svikin's Stand.

Title: Glacial Enchainment
Description: An Enchainment: A combination chain of steps leading to Mourningdale.

Title: Frigid Relevé
Description: A Relevé: To rise with a small upwards action starting with bent knees in Periville.

Title: Wintry Pirouette
Description: A Pirouette: To turn in dance towards Stone Skull Fort.

Title: Bitter Battement
Description: A Battement: A movement with a closing action towards Eridanus.

Title: Snowy Sissonne
Description: A Scissone: A jump from two feet to two feet in Mangled Heights.

Title: The Tempest's Soul (Expedition)
Description: Enter Tempest's Heart and Defeat Isabella De Leon.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Precisely. You have no doubt heard of the Tempest and have come seeking her ruin. But what do you know of Captain Isabella? What does anyone know? \n\nI intend to discover what madness drove her to this point.
InProgressResponse: I have found accounts scattered across this island by those who had contact with Isabella. The story they tell is grim. \n\nBut this place can reveal which accounts were true and which were false.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So it is true… Isabella De Leon is no more. This is only the beginning. \n\nTo fully understand how a god-fearing, upstanding citizen of Spain could become such a monster will require delving deeper into Isabella's reality.

Title: Isabella De Leon (Expedition)
Description: Find out about Isabella's past in Spain with her brothers. Then defeat Isabella De Leon again with this new knowledge in mind.
PlayerPrompt: "I'd never given any thought to her parents."
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
We all have family. She also had brothers. Could they have stopped Isabella's descent into madness? 

I myself am an only child. I often wished for the love and comfort of a sibling, to help ease my woes. 

Were her brothers of any help?
InProgressResponse: I am curious to know whether our ill-fated Captain had help or hindrance from her brothers. \n\nI have wondered this for a long time…
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, so Philip and Cosimo squandered their fortune and family name away. It's no wonder Isabella became so isolated and desperate. \n\nI had hoped she would've found some comfort in family. Perhaps I was naïve. It would not be the first time.

Title: Isabella's Corruption (Expedition)
Description: Find out about how Isabella was offered the mantle of Corruption. Then defeat Isabella De Leon with this new knowledge in mind.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: But how can we know for sure? \n\nI used to be a sister of the cloth before my arrival on Aeternum. If there is even the slightesst hope for Isabella's soul, then I must know if she resisted the Heretic.
InProgressResponse: I left my convent to discover all I could about Isabella. The rumors of her fate frightened me. But they also piqued my interest. \n\nCould such a place as Aeternum truly exist?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: It was a swift downfall then. Isabella ate the forbidden fruit with no remorse. This is... disheartening. \n\nI had heard so many stories of her kindness, her nobility, her courage in the face of adversity.

Title: Rise of Captain Isabella (Expedition)
Description: Find out about Isabella's descent into cruelty with her crew by investigating the graves where they were buried alive. Then defeat Isabella De Leon with this new knowledge in mind.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Still, I must believe that some part of the noble woman remained. \n\nSurely there must have been a place in her heart for someone? A person dear to her?
InProgressResponse: Please discover more about Isabella's trek across the island. \n\nWas it true her crew mutinied? A captain would have to punish mutineers, wouldn't they?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: She buried them alive? Oh God, she condemned them to the earth, a terrible fate on Aeternum. \n\nHow could she have done this?

Title: Death of the Heretic (Expedition)
Description: Find out about the Heretic's true power and talk to the Heretic. Then defeat Isabella De Leon with this new knowledge in mind.
PlayerPrompt: "You seem determined to prove this wasn't her fault."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: She was misled! That much I know for sure. Is the Heretic the source of Corruption? That would explain it. \n\nThat is the only way to explain my aunt's transformation! The monster in these tales does not match the woman I knew.
InProgressResponse: Aunt Isabella was as beautiful as an angel. She was devout and prayed at Church often. \n\nIt was she who inspired me to pursue life at the convent. She was a saint to me.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You bring me a name I have never heard before: Nedenyek. It chills my very soul. \n\nIs that the Heretic's true name? It must be the name of the Devil himself! The Beast!

Title: The Possession of Russo (Expedition)
Description: Find out the truth about Isabella and Father Russo, and what is to come, and talk to Father Russo. Then defeat Isabella De Leon with this new knowledge in mind.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I do not know. Perhaps it is as you said - Isabella had no one. \n\nWhat a tragic possibility. To feel utterly alone in the world...
InProgressResponse: In another life, perhaps Father Russo and Isabella could have been together. We will never know.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So she turned away from Father Russo, who loved her with all of his heart. \n\nMy aunt is truly lost to me. I will say a prayer for her soul.

Title: Isabella's Madness (Expedition)
Description: Recover a shard of Isabella's madness in the ashes of her defeat for Mara Rosa to study.
PlayerPrompt: "So her example will serve as a lesson?"
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That seems just.\n\nMy Aunt Isabella deserves to have her story told and understood in its entirety. We must leave nothing out.
InProgressResponse:
Have you collected another Shard of Madness? 

Perhaps these memories will help point a way toward her salvation someday. 

We must always have hope.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: This Shard of Madness is full of pain. I shall store it with the others. \n\nPerhaps one day, Aeternum shall have a full portrait of the woman I knew. The captain, the legend, the terror: Isabella De Leon.
